"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is incorrectly using Matplotlib's date functionality. The `MonthLocator` and `DateFormatter` are being set after the xticks and xticklabels have been manually set. This will override the locator and formatter settings. Instead, the locator and formatter should be set before plotting the data.\",\n  \"patch\": \"17,20c17,20\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n< ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(MonthLocator())\\n< ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%Y-%m'))\\n---\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(MonthLocator())\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%Y-%m'))\\n> fig.autofmt_xdate(rotation=45)\\n> # Remove ax.set_xticks and ax.set_xticklabels lines\"\n}"